&lt;h3&gt;Rosh Chodesh Av&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Traditionally, people take on additional mourning practices in the nine days between Rosh Chodesh Av and Tisha b&#039;Av. These practices include not eating meat or drinking wine and not cutting one&#039;s hair. All mourning practices are suspended on Shabbat. For a Reform perspective on this period, see JL 129-130.&lt;/p&gt;
